Definition.WordDefinition:
Good-looking \Good"-look`ing\, a. Handsome; fine-looking; as, a good-looking man.
Syn: fine-looking, better-looking, handsome, well-favored, well-favoured. [1913 Webster + WordNet 1.5]

good-looking adj : pleasing in appearance especially by reason of conformity to ideals of form and proportion; "a fine-looking woman"; "a good-looking man"; "better-looking than her sister"; "very pretty but not so extraordinarily handsome"- Thackeray; "our southern women are well-favored"- Lillian Hellman [syn: {fine-looking}, {better-looking}, {handsome}, {well-favored}, {well-favoured}]
